CatDescriptText: Mamie Turner, housewife, Mt. Pleasant, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 21, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that the steel strike will be resumed after the 80-day 'cooling-off' period imposed by the Supreme Court under the injection of the Taft-Hartley Act?" answer reads: "I don't think that it will be necessary, because it probably will be settled by that time."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Mamie Turner wearing dark tweed coat and light colored patterned head scarf, posed in front of brick wall
